The Met Office has issued 82 flood warnings throughout the country amid high risk of rain and storm. The warning for today reads: "Heavy rain bringing the chance of some flooding and disruption." In terms of what to expect, the warning adds: "Flooding of a few homes and businesses is likely." It also says that bus and train services are likely to be disrupted alongside disruption to power supplies other supplies. Met Office have given this a yellow warning, which can be issued for a range of weather situations. Many are issued when it is likely that the weather will cause some low level impacts, including some disruption to travel in a few places. Areas affected include Derbyshire in the East Midlands, Durham in the North East, Blackburn with Darwen Blackpool, Cumbria, Greater Manchester, Lancashire, and Merseyside in the North West. In the South West, it includes Cornwall, Devon, Dorset, Gloucestershire, Plymouth, Somerset, South Gloucestershire, Swindon, Torbay, Wiltshire. The weather warning reads: "Outbreaks of rain, heavy at times, will move in from the southwest on Friday evening then persist overnight into Saturday. "20 to 30 mm rain is likely quite widely with 40 to 50 mm on some hills." "With conditions already very wet this is likely to cause some flooding. "The rain will also be accompanied by strong winds, with gusts of 40-50 mph and possibly 60 mph on some exposed coasts in the south. The rain and strong winds will clear eastwards during Saturday daytime." We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. For the latest news and breaking news visit: /news Stay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you. Follow our social media accounts here on facebook.com/DailyExpress and @daily_express.